      "writtenOn": "2019-08-16T19:11:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The scenario I try to avoid is: \n\n1. We deploy a lucicfg change that introduces formatting difference.\n2. Now everyones PRESUBMIT.py complain that *.cfg files on disk are out-of-date, even if they didn\u0027t touch anything.\n\nI guess I can make `lucicfg generate` to always imply \"force\" and `lucicfg validate` to always imply \"non-force\". It will solve my concern, but it will introduce a quirk: `lucicfg validate` tells that all files are up-to-date, but `lucicfg generate` still produces non-empty (but semantically insignificant) diff.\n\nWhat do you think? At least it will guarantee that all files are formatted in a consistent style.",
      "parentUuid": "dcb53066_20d9d93c",
